<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-09-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-09-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="561" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d561">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/1282.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Gonzales</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-09-01">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 1, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Sub-Secretary of State informs Scholle that Bobo, Haitian revolutionist,
                            has debarked at Santiago de Cuba after being refused admission at Santo
                            Domingo. The Cuban Government is having him closely watched as there are
                            many Haitians in Cuba and Government wishes to frustrate any
                            revolutionary propaganda in Cuba.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>